llations of silicene are highly sensitive to the concentration of\ninjected or ejected charge carriers. More importantly, the two-dimensional and\nacoustic plasmons appear to be a signature of the honeycomb lattice,\nindependently of the chemistry of the group-IV elements and the details of the\nunit-cell geometry.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 12 Oct 2016 09:48:51 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 24 Jan 2017 07:54:53 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 16 Feb 2017 08:33:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-02-17"}
